<br>
There seems to be two systems people use to distribute loot in EQ. <br>
<br>
Randoming items so its &quot;fair&quot; reguardless of participation within the guild or need of item.  Well there are additional problems with this system.  Example, when a level 50 character wins a high level BP who rarely participates in guild raids especially when no loot drops for his class.  So by winning this nice item the guild will rarely benefit from it.  <br>
<br>
Using a loot council system or have loot system which does not use /rand.  This system has advantages depending how its laid out.<br>
<br>
In Vision, we use Class Leaders and Officers primarily to determine who gets what loot.  For the Shadow Knight class for example its primarily based on:<br>
1)Guild Participation (Raids and Events)<br>
2)Shadow Knight Level<br>
3)Need<br>
<br>
